The paper deals with graph generative models, which are a popular topic in machine learning and data mining. The use of LSTM architecture and the focus on learning joint distributions suggest that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also addresses the issue of scalability, which is a common concern in the field of databases, making cs.DB (Databases) another likely sub-category. The paper's focus on learning semantic labels and the use of canonical labels suggest that it may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper's emphasis on experimentation and evaluation suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
